  "texts": [
    "We provide opinions of distilled data through presentations and publications rather than direct access to data.",
    "To reap the benefits of ecological and environmental synthesis, we must address the technological and sociocultural barriers that have impeded free access to data.",
    "While \"open data\" will improve and accelerate scientific progress, there is also a need for \"open science, \" which preserves not just data but also analyses and techniques, resulting in greater openness and repeatability of discoveries.",
    "It has been emphasized that environmental research programs should attempt to reach a bigger audience that more accurately represents society.",
    "Furthermore, scientists must be more open to engaging with the general public and communicating science in a clearer and simpler manner, such as by avoiding jargon and communicating in ways that are clearer and more intelligible to non-specialists."
